data.description: Overview of the drug development process from discovery to investigational new drug application (IND). Drug discovery (target identification, target validation, and hit-to-lead) preclinical CMC activities, and preclinical pharmacology, pharmacokinetic, and toxicology studies as they apply to both small and large molecule drugs.
data.title: THE DRUG DEVELOPMENT PROCESS FROM DISCOVERY TO INVESTIGATIONAL NEW DRUG APPLICATION (IND)
